This article summarizes remarks made by President Mahmoud Abbas of Palestine and President Donald Trump during a joint press conference in Bethlehem. President Abbas welcomed President Trump and condemned the recent terrorist attack in Manchester. He expressed hope for a lasting and justice-based peace deal with Israel, while emphasizing the importance of the two-state solution and the recognition of the state of Palestine. President Abbas also called for the humane treatment of Palestinian prisoners and highlighted the issue of occupation and settlements. President Trump offered his prayers and condolences to the victims of the Manchester attack and expressed solidarity with the people of the United Kingdom. He reiterated his commitment to achieving peace between Israelis and Palestinians and praised the leaders of the Muslim world for their efforts to combat terrorism. President Trump emphasized the need to obliterate the ideology of terrorism and protect innocent lives. He also expressed his willingness to work with President Abbas on improving the Palestinian economy and continuing counterterrorism efforts.